OL,5,G0110 Secrets of the Royal Palaces
OL,6,     FHighgrove House, Gloucester, is
OL,7,     Fthe smallest royal residence
OL,8,     Fcurrently in use, with nine
OL,9,     Fbedrooms. It is King Charles's own
OL,10,     Fcreation, featuring a garden
OL,11,     Fdescribed as an 'organic oasis'.
OL,12,G0210 Secrets of the Royal Palaces
OL,13,     FThe secrets of eight famous royal
OL,14,     Fpalaces. Christopher Wren expanded
OL,15,     Fthe former Nottingham House into a
OL,16,     Fpalace, which some describe as a
OL,17,     Fbit of a 'botched job'.
